EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to natural resources; providing, with certain
exceptions, that any person is authorized to perform
certain actions relating to an easement for conservation;
and providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law authorizes, with certain exceptions, an easement for conservation
2 to be created, conveyed, recorded, assigned, released, modified, terminated or
3 otherwise altered or affected in the same manner as other easements. (NRS
4 111.420) This bill instead provides that any person, including a state or local
5 government or any agency or instrumentality thereof, is authorized to create,
6 convey, record, assign, release, reserve, modify, terminate or otherwise alter or
7 affect an easement for conservation in the same manner as other easements.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. NRS 111.420 is hereby amended to read as follows:
2 111.420 1. Except as otherwise provided in NRS 111.390 to
3 111.440, inclusive, [an] any person, including, without limitation,
4 a state or local government or any agency or instrumentality
5 thereof, may create, convey, record, assign, release, reserve,
6 modify, terminate or otherwise alter or affect an easement for
7 conservation [may be created, conveyed, recorded, assigned,
8 released, modified, terminated or otherwise altered or affected] in
9 the same manner as other easements.
